    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Cut the<strong> aubergine</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> in half lengthways</p> <p>Score the flesh quite deeply (in a criss-cross pattern) taking care not the cut the skin&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-glazed-aubergine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>lemon</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> in half&nbsp;</p> <p>Combine the <strong>harissa paste</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>lemon</strong>&nbsp;juice and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> - this is your<strong> harissa glaze</strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-glazed-aubergine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> bulgur</strong>&nbsp;to a pot of plenty of <strong>salted</strong> <strong>boiled water</strong></p> <p>Cook for 10-18 min or until the bulgur is tender with a slight bite&nbsp;</p> <p>Once cooked, drain and set aside to cool slightly&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-glazed-aubergine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the&nbsp;<strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;</span>to a baking tray, cut-side up (use tin foil to avoid mess!)</p> <p>Spoon 3/4 of the <strong>harissa glaze</strong> over the cut side of the aubergines</p> <p>Put the baking tray in the oven for 15 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-glazed-aubergine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p> <p>Strip the<strong> mint leaves</strong> from the stems and chop the leaves finely, discarding the stems&nbsp;</p> <p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onions</strong> finely</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-glazed-aubergine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bulgur has cooled slightly, add the chopped <strong>mint</strong>, <strong>parsley&nbsp;</strong>and <strong>spring onions</strong></p> <p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Squeeze in 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> lemon</strong> <strong>juice</strong> and stir to combine - this is your <strong>herby tabbouleh</strong>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-glazed-aubergine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once they've had 15 min, spoon the <strong>remaining glaze</strong> over the<strong> aubergine</strong> halves and return them to the oven for a further 8-10 min or until the aubergine&nbsp;is soft and the glaze is sticky</p> <p>Cut the remaining<strong> lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-glazed-aubergine/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the harissa-glazed aubergine over the herby tabbouleh&nbsp;</p> <p>Crumble the feta over&nbsp;and serve with a lemon wedge to the side&nbsp;</p> <p>Enjoy!</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
